  "text": "Further extensive differences in gene expression between immature and repair Schwann cells are indicated in a study comparing developing and regenerating nerves [CITATION_1] ). This work identified over a hundred genes that were regulated distal to nerve crush, although these genes were not developmentally regulated, being expressed at similar levels in newborn and adult uninjured nerves. Most of these genes were up-regulated after injury, suggesting that induction of a large number of injury-specific genes is one of the features that differentiate repair Schwann cells from cells in developing nerves prior to myelination.",
